UNITED STATES of America ex rel. Gene McCANN, Petitioner-Appellant, v. James E. MULCAHY, United States Marshal for the Southern District of New York, and E. E. Thompson, Warden of the United States Detention Headquarters, 427 West Street, New York City, Respondents-Appellees. No. 187. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit Feb. 1, 1946. Gene McCann, petitioner-appellant pro se. John F. X. McGohey, U. S.. Atty., of New York City (John J. Donovan, Jr., of New York City, of counsel), for respondents-appellees.

Before SWAN, CHASE, and CLARK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed.
